description:
The Ultimate Collection Never Forget - Take That [2005]




As the most popular teen pop sensation in Britain since the '60s, Take That ruled the U.K. charts during the first half of the '90s. In strict commercial terms, the band sold more records than any English act since the Beatles, though the cultural and musical importance was significantly less substantial. Conceived as a British answer to New Kids on the Block, Take That initially worked the same territory as their American counterparts, singing watered-down new jack R&B, urban soul, and mainstream pop.

They were the first band since the Beatles to score four consecutive number one singles with "Pray", "Relight My Fire", "Babe", and "Everything Changes" and the first act to release eight singles entering the UK chart at Number 1. This new compilation features all the hits and a live rendition of "Pray" and the new "Relight My Fire" (Element 2006 Remix).
